<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-MODESTI-COLUMN-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ONE BIG RIVALRY, TWO GREAT MINDS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEVIN MODESTI  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Jose Bruin and Tommy Trojan meet for a preseason
lunch on neutral ground in Hollywood, where a talking bear and a
guy in a skirt can get a table without much fuss.
</P>
<P>
   ``Did you hurt yourself?'' Tommy says.
</P>
<P>
   ``Hurt myself? Oh, you refer to my cane,'' Jose says. ``It's
nothing serious.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Comes in handy when you park in those blue spaces, huh?''
</P>
<P>
   A testy silence.
</P>
<P>
   ``Look here,'' says Tommy, who sounds a bit like John Wayne,
``the reason I invited you _''
</P>
<P>
   ``What do you mean, you invited me?'' Jose growls. ``(begin
ital)I(end ital) invited (begin ital)you(end ital)!''
</P>
<P>
   ``Well let's not argue about trivialities. I was thinking it
would be nice if we sat down and ironed out our differences.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought the same thing. We really should get along better
than we have.''
</P>
<P>
   ``We're neighbors, after all.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Civilized folk.''
</P>
<P>
   ``And we share a noble objective.''
</P>
<P>
   ``To educate and mold young people.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Exactly.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Especially young people who run a 4.5-second 40.''
</P>
<P>
   ``So why should we fight?''
</P>
<P>
   ``Why indeed.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Just because you're a quiche-eating socialist?''
</P>
<P>
   ``Just because you're Daddy's Little Rich Boy?''
</P>
<P>
   ``Let's not dwell on petty differences.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Not when, more than ever, our football programs should feel
sympathetic toward each other, not antagonistic.''
</P>
<P>
   ``My sentiments exactly!''
</P>
<P>
   ``I mean, this year, nobody can tell the Bruins and Trojans
apart. It's as if there's been a role-reversal or something.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Right,'' Tommy says. ``Everybody got used to UCLA having the
hotshot quarterbacks and SC settling for anybody with two arms. But
now we're the ones with the strapping young quarterback who's on
the cover of all the preview magazines, and you guys had to choose
a starter from Drew Bennett, Cory Paus and the ballboy.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Don't remind me,'' Jose says quietly.
</P>
<P>
   ``I know how it feels, my excessively hairy friend.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Tell me, what (begin ital)was(end ital) the Reggie Perry era
like, anyway?''
</P>
<P>
   ``Reggie Perry is the reason I sympathize with you.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's as if our offensive teams have traded places. Your
Trojans are talking about mixing it up, piling up the points. My
Bruins are talking about keeping it simple, not confusing the
passer.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I've been there.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Here's another switch. Remember how bad our defense was last
year? Well, now the coach is actually talking about the linebackers
being a strength of the team! Meanwhile, your Trojans played
defense like a brick wall last year, and this year the coach
actually used the word `turmoil' to describe the situation there.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Good thing we don't have to play Miami, huh?''
</P>
<P>
   ``Miami is the reason (begin ital)I(end ital) sympathize with
(begin ital)you(end ital).''
</P>
<P>
   ``You guys really took a beating in the press over that game,
didn't you? It was like us in the old days when we were on top, the
expectations that used to follow us around. If SC didn't go
undefeated, there was an investigation.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Times sure have changed. I heard one of your players
predicting SC would beat us this year. He said he wanted to try to
get a rivalry going! It sounded like us in the old days _ we had to
remind people there are two teams in town.''
</P>
<P>
   ``You're really a smart guy, you know that?'' Tommy says with
mock admiration. ``Almost made me forget it's USC that was just
chosen as `College of the Year' by the Time-Princeton Review, not
UCLA.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I think I read that somewhere,'' Jose says. ``That's either a
colossal turnabout or a typographical error. Anyway, that's the
kind of thing I'm talking about when I say it's hard to tell the
Bruins from the Trojans anymore. I mean, USC is suddenly a vaunted
academic institution...''
</P>
<P>
   ``While UCLA's football players get hauled off to court. I sure
do know how bad that feels. By the way, I hear they're changing the
handicapped parking placards from blue and white to blue and
gold.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Cute. I hear O.J.'s going back to campus to coach the golf
team.''
</P>
<P>
   An uncomfortable silence.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm glad we got together like this. It reminded me how much I
really detest you.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Just one more thing we have in common.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
