<HEADLINE>
COLEMAN MAKES A SPLASH WITHOUT `SWIMMING'
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Early in training camp, when the UCLA coaches
issued a ``no swimming'' edict, no one was happier than defensive
end Kenyon Coleman. Although he loves to swim, Coleman knew it
wasn't in his best interest.
</P>
<P>
   The proclamation had nothing to do with swimming pools or
