   CHILDREN-LICE (Albany, N.Y.) _ Every parent dreads a phone call
from the school nurse, but anxiety is compounded by disgust when
the problem is head lice. Head lice is one of the most common
childhood problems. This year, up to 20 million people in the
United States are expected to become infected, with the majority of
cases in children under 12.
</P>
<P>
   TV-FASHION (San Francisco) _ One of the major pleasures of
watching ``Sex and the City'' on HBO is to see what the women will
be wearing from week to week. And their ``looks'' are no accident _
they're very carefully put together by a pair of women named Field:
Patricia Field, well-known for her Greenwich Village shop, and her
partner, Rebecca Field (no relation). By CYNTHIA ROBINS.
</P>
<P>
   SUNFLOWERS (Albany, N.Y.) _ Many kinds of flowering plants turn
toward the sun. But none captivate and mystify the way a field of
8-foot stalks topped with yellow disks do. The wide flat circles of
sunflowers seem to both follow the sun and reflect its image. By
CELINA OTTAWAY.
