<SLUG> BC-FALLBOOKS-OTHERS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OTHER FALL BOOKS TO WATCH FOR
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies FALL BOOKS) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The fall books season invariably includes entries from familiar
names as well as intriguing titles from authors whose names may not
be household words even in their own households. Here are brief
descriptions and publication dates of other notable books you'll
see on the shelves in the coming months:
</P>
<P>
   ``Hearts in Atlantis,'' by Stephen King (Scribner, $27,
September) _ The Vietnam War exacts its toll on several veterans;
also, a dollop of dark, nasty magic.
</P>
<P>
   ``All the Best, George Bush,'' by George Bush (Scribner, $27.50,
October) _ The former president publishes some of his letters. It
could be a sleeper bestseller.
</P>
<P>
   ``Dune: House Atreides,'' by Brian Herbert (Bantam, $27.50,
October) _ Son of ``Dune'' author Frank Herbert tries to rekindle
interest in talky sci-fi.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mankind: Have a Nice Day,'' by Mick Foley (ReganBooks, $22,
October) _ First Jesse the Body. Now, we've come to this: Another
pro wrestler's autobiography.
</P>
<P>
   ``Everybody Smokes in Hell,'' by John Ridley (Knopf, $23,
September) _ Clever comic novel deserves your attention.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Junction Boys: How 10 Days in Hell With Bear Bryant Forged
a Champion Team at Texas A&AMP;M,'' by Jim Dent (St. Martin's, $24.95,
September) _ You won't believe what you read about the legendary
Bear. Amazing stuff.
</P>
<P>
   ``Fountain Society,'' by Wes Craven _ (Simon &AMP; Schuster, $25,
October) _ ``Scream'' director tries his hand at print
entertainment. Guess which genre?
</P>
<P>
   ``The Running Kind,'' by Merle Haggard with Tom Carter
(HarperCollins, $24, November) _ It might be good, but someone else
will have to make that assessment.
</P>
<P>
   ``Timeline,'' by Michael Crichton (Knopf, $26.95, November) _ As
usual, the publisher won't reveal anything about this novel until
publication. Crichton fans wait breathlessly.
</P>
<P>
   ``Larry L. King: A Writer's Life in Letters, or, Reflections
From a Bloodshot Eye,'' by Larry L. King (TCU Press, $24.50,
October) _ Full-blooded and a whole lot of fun, just like
everything else King has written.
</P>
<P>
   ``John Glenn: A Memoir,'' by John Glenn (Bantam, $27, November)
_ Sorry, but Americans find him interesting only when he's in
orbit.
</P>
<P>
   _ Jeff Guinn
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
