<HEADLINE>
IT WAS A DARK AND STORMY ... OH, NEVER MIND
</HEADLINE>
Bc-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: .MDNM/I'm trying to identify the novel and author of the
following quote, ``It was a dark and stormy night on the west coast
of Scotland.'' I'm informed it is from a nonsense novel. Can you
help? _ D.R., via the Internet
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ That's the opening sentence of ``Gertrude the
Governess,'' a story by humorist Stephen Leacock from his 1911 book
``Nonsense Novels.''
</P>
<P>
   The story's next line: ``This, however, is immaterial to the
present story, as the scene is not laid in the West of Scotland.''
</P>
<P>
   Another memorable quote from the same story: ``Lord Ronald said
nothing; he flung himself from the room, flung himself upon his
horse and rode madly off in all directions.''
</P>
<P>
   Leacock, who lived from 1869 to 1944, wrote several humorous
books and essays and headed the McGill University political science
and economics department for many years.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ I'd like to write to Anthony Quinn, the actor and
artist, to inform him about the popularity of his work in my
country. How can I contact him? _ M.B., Secunderabad, India
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ Write to Quinn at Box 479, Bristol, RI 02809-0479.
</P>
<P>
   Quinn, 84, has been exhibiting art since the early '80s. In
December, he teamed with his son, Lorenzo, to display more than 90
works in Seoul, Korea.
</P>
<P>
   His next film appearance is likely to be in ``Ringside,'' a film
directed by Norman Mailer that also stars Paul Sorvino and Halle
Berry.
</P>
<P>
   One explanation for Quinn's six-decade, two-profession career:
13 children with five women, including 3- and 5-year-olds with his
current wife, Kathy Benvin.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ Was George Hamilton ever a member of ``The A-Team,''
the series with Mr. T? _ T.G., Brownwood
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ The only George on the team was Peppard, who played
Col. John ``Hannibal'' Smith.
</P>
<P>
   The other members were Dirk Benedict as Templeton ``Faceman''
Peck, Dwight Schultz as H.M. ``Howling Mad'' Murdock and Mr. T as
Bosco ``Bad Attitude'' Baracus.
</P>
<P>
   The NBC series aired from 1983 to 1987.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
