<HEADLINE>
TEST YOUR LITERARY KNOWLEDGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   This multiple-choice exercise focuses on classic American
poetry. It's tricky, so you pass with only nine correct answers and
earn an A with 12 right.
</P>
<P>
   1. William Cullen Bryant wrote (a) ``Monument Mountain;''
(b)Thanatopsis;'' (c) ``To a Waterfowl;'' (d) all of the above.
</P>
<P>
   2. Emily Dickinson wrote poem(s) beginning with the lines, (a)
``I taste a liquor never brewed ...'' (b) ``Into my heart a blow
that kills ...'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   3. T.S. Eliot wrote (a) ``Ash Wednesday;'' (b) ``The Last Ride
Together;'' (c) ``Patterns;'' (d) none of the above.
</P>
<P>
   4. Oliver Wendell Holmes Sr. wrote (a) ``The Chambered
Nautilus;'' (b) ``Old Ironsides;'' (c) both of the above; (d)
neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   5. Robert Frost wrote (a) ``A House by the Side of the Road;''
(b) ``The Road Not Taken;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of
the above.
</P>
<P>
   6. Julia Ward Howe wrote (a) ``Battle Hymn of the Republic;''
(b) ``Passion Flowers;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the
above.
</P>
<P>
   7. Langston Hughes wrote (a) ``Shakespeare in Harlem;'' (b)
``Montage of a Dream Deferred;'' (c) ``Ask Your Mama;'' (d) all of
the above.
</P>
<P>
   8. Sidney Lanier wrote (a) ``The Lake Isle of Inisfree;'' (b)
``The Marshes of Glynn;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the
above.
</P>
<P>
   9. Henry Wadsworth Longfellow wrote (a) ``To a Wild
Honeysuckle;'' (b) ``A Psalm of Life;'' (c) both of the above; (d)
neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   10. James Russell Lowell wrote (a) ``Evangeline;'' (b) ``Little
Boy Blue;'' (c) ``Skipper Ireson's Ride;'' (d) none of the above.
</P>
<P>
   11. Edgar Lee Masters wrote (a) ``Highland Mary;'' (b) Miniver
Cheevy;'' (c) ``The Man With the Hoe;'' (d) none of the above.
</P>
<P>
   12. Edna St. Vincent Millay wrote (a) ``Recuerdo;'' (b)
``Renascence;'' (c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   13. Edwin Arlington Robinson wrote (a) ``The Man Against the
Sky;'' (b) ``Mr. Flood's Party,'' (c) ``Richard Corey'' (d) all of
the above.
</P>
<P>
   14. Carl Sandburg wrote (a) ``Grass;'' (b) ``Smoke and Steel;''
(c) both of the above; (d) neither of the above.
</P>
<P>
   15. Sara Teasdale wrote (a) ``Dark of the Moon;'' (b) ``Flame
and Shadow;'' (c) ``Sonnets to Duse;'' (d) all of the above.
</P>
<P>
   16. John Greenleaf Whittier wrote (a) ``A Ballad for Maud;'' (b)
``Maud;'' (c) ``Maud Muller;'' (d) all of the above.
</P>
<P>
   Quiz answers: 1-d; 2-a; 3-a; 4-c; 5-b; 6-c; 7-d; 8-b; 9-b; 10-d;
11-d; 12-c; 13-d; 14-c; 15-d; 16-c.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
