<P>
   COKE-SOUTHAFRICA _ATLANTA _ Coca-Cola Co. is expected to receive
government approval in South Africa for its deal to acqure
Cadbury-Schweppes's brands in that country. (Unger, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   COX-MP3 _ Cox Interactive Media and MP3.com announce their first
joint venture Tuesday at the NAB (national association of
broadcasters.) (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   INSURE _ATLANTA _Georgia's insurance premium tax _ one of the
nation's highest _ is a big money-maker for both state and local
governments. However, critics of the tax both in and outside the
industry say it has stymied Atlanta's development as an insurance
hub much the way the state's archiac bank branching laws caused
Atlanta to lose the region's major banks to North Carolina.
(Manitus, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BIZMAGS _ A rundown of the week's financial press. (Walker,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
