   BB0-UMPS _ ATLANTA _ The umpire controversy in major-league
baseball is expected to reach its peak today, when several
long-time umps get the thumb. Two local umpires have felt the
impact: Paul Nauert worked his entire life to become a major-league
umpire, then four months into his dream job, he joining group of
umpires who turned in resignations, effective today. He's history.
Recently hired Marvin Hudson also dreamed of being a major-league
ump. His ``replacement'' status becomes ``permanent'' this evening.
(Stinson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
