<HEADLINE>
BURNS THINKS WIN AGAINST TAMPA POSSIBLE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By FRANK DELL'APA  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WELLESLEY, Mass. _ Revolution captain Mike Burns agrees the team
needs to make changes next year. But Burns is also optimistic about
salvaging this season by winning Saturday against Tampa Bay.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's the same old story,'' Burns said Wednesday. ``We are
going to need a complete overhaul, even if we make the playoffs.
But, to be objective, you can't completely change all 22 players.
You have to keep some.
</P>
<P>
   ``The players who want to be here should be here and the ones
who don't want to be here should move on _ and that is not
necessarily a bad thing. They might want to leave the league or go
to another MLS team.
</P>
<P>
   ``Change is sometimes good. This situation affects the
perception of players. Some players who are in D.C. are regarded as
better players than they are, but here some players are regarded as
worse players than they are.''
</P>
<P>
   Burns began playing soccer in his native Marlborough, Mass., has
been with the US national team for two World Cups, and had
exceptional success in Copa America '95, US Cup '95, and CONCACAF
Gold Cup '97. But Burns has not had similar success with his
hometown professional team.
</P>
<P>
   ``This has been frustrating to the point of embarrassment,''
Burns said. ``We've been behind the 8-ball since Day 1. We've had
four terrible years. But I said this at the start of the season,
I've been here for the bad and I want to be here when we turn it
around.''
</P>
<P>
   The Revolution have used 67 players in four seasons, and many of
Burns's former teammates have gone on to have successful careers
elsewhere. Meanwhile, the Revolution have been consistently near
the bottom of the Eastern Conference standings.
</P>
<P>
   ``Most of the people who have been involved deserve some
criticism, but some are not as much to blame as others,'' Burns
said. ``In the past, the chemistry has not been good. But with this
team, the chemistry is not bad.
</P>
<P>
   ``The main thing now is that we are 3 points out of the playoffs
and everyone is thinking in the back of their mind that, after
losing eight of nine games, that is pretty remarkable. If we were
not in the playoff race, a lot of guys might have packed it in and
thrown away the season. Now, if we win, we are right back in it.
But we have to win this weekend or else the season is virtually
over.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
