<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the additional
story for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Thursday, Sept. 2, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Veronica Villarreal at (206) 448-8342.
</P>
<P>
   BEANIE BABIES (Seattle) _ It's got the making of a kid's mystery
flick. Big toy company says Butch the Bull Terrier, Goochy the
Ty-dye Jellyfish and Kuku the Cockatoo are off to the Big Playpen
In The Sky; fans flock the phone lines and scream, ``Say it ain't
so!''; company honchos keep mum except for a cryptic message:
``VERY IMPORTANT NOTICE _ On December 31, 1999 at 11:59 p.m.
(Central Time) All Beanies will be retired''. The ``Great Beanies
Caper'' continued to unfold Wednesday, as tens of thousands of
collectors of the cuddly, cute Beanie Babies toys called up stores
and surfed the Web, looking to learn if the end of the century will
also spell the end one of the hottest toy crazes of this decade.
</P>
<P>
   By Robert L. Jamieson Jr. (Story will move in the ``l'' and
``a'' categories.)
</P>
