<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Web health site joins with Cox Interactive
 &HT;    By Frances Katz
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Two major health portals, Cybear and HealthAtoZ,
launched a Web site Wednesday called Solutionshealth.com.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to its own Web site, Solutionshealth has teamed with
Cox Interactive Media to offer the new portal to users of its 24
city sites including Access Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Access Atlanta will feature a link to Solutionshealth.com.
</P>
<P>
   Cox Interactive Media is a subsidiary of Cox Enterprises, parent
company of The Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   ``Cybear's Solutionshealth.com and healthAtoZ.com will help
bring customized, credible, and timely health care information to
the local communities we serve,'' said CIM President Peter Winter,
in a statement. ``By localizing and going one step further to
personalize health care information, we make it even more valuable
to our consumers.''
</P>
<P>
   In addition to health news, the new Web site will also keep
track of addresses, medications, diet and exercise regimes and
other personal medical information.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
