<HEADER>
A7853 &Cx1f; tad-z
u l BC-MONICA-BAGS02-COX     09-01 0230
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MONICA-BAGS02-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Monica packs up troubles in a bold knit bag
 &HT;    By Staci Sturrock
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Monica Lewinsky is bagging it all.
</P>
<P>
   In an attempt to make a silk purse out of her sow's ear of a
professional life, the former White House intern has launched her
own line of purses and totes on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   Her latest incarnation as fashion designer began when she
learned to knit in the aftermath of her affair with President
Clinton.
</P>
<P>
   ``Once I survived the frustrating stages of dropping every other
stitch, it became a new form of relaxation,'' she explains on her
Web site: www.TheRealMonicaInc.com. ``However, I lacked a
fundamental tool essential to every knitter _ the knitting bag.''
</P>
<P>
   Unable to find a bag that she liked, the plucky 25-year-old
decided to sew her own. ``I began designing bags using beautiful
and exquisite materials, and I tried to make unique and artistic
combinations.''
</P>
<P>
   Combinations such as black velvet, crimson velvet, faux-fur
leopard print and black-and-rose brocade _ all in one handbag! Each
purse and tote also features a flowery tag that reads, ``Made
especially for you by Monica.''
</P>
<P>
   The eight bags range in price from $70 to $130.
</P>
<P>
   (All bags, incidentally, are dry clean only.)
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
