onto a field in southern Sudan in April. Depriving citizens of food
is a vicious tool of modern warfare. And in Sudan, a poor country
in East Africa, the government is using hunger as a weapon. Because
international relief now plays such a large role in war, concern is
growing that in the rush to aid the afflicted, the relief may be
abetting those who have a stake in the conflict. (Andrew
Innerarity/Houston Chronicle Photo)
