   (NYT104) PANTHOU, Sudan -- Sept. 1, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., SEPT.
5 -- SUDAN-AID-4-HNS, 09-01 -- Abuk Garang, 12, scrabbles to
collect grains of cereal spilled on the ground after a food drop
from aircraft with the United Nations relief effort in April.
Established 10 years ago to aid the vicitms of Sudan's intractable,
16-year-old civil war, the U.N.-led operation has been unable to
eradicate hunger, a preferred weapon in the conflict. (Andrew
Innerarity/Houston Chronicle Photo)
